TextEng: Make me more powerful by your magic!
Text: 네 마법으로 날 더 강하게 만들어!

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> I require the assistance of a magic item!
<StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> I command you to give me an item of the greatest power!
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 가장 강력한 아이템을 내게 주라 명한다!

TextEng: I come as the Judge and demand only answers.
Uh, you make me big and tuff!
Text: 어, 너 나 크고 강하게 만들어!

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> Uh, me need a... a magic thingy!
<StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> Me need a magic thingy. Somethin' of great power!
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 나 마법 물건 필요해. 엄청 강한 거!

TextEng: Me be da Judge-guy. Me only want answers.
Then tell me the tale of the brothers Jhareg...
What charade do you speak of?
Were you a witness or a participant in this crime?
Text: 넌 이 범죄의 목격자였어, 아니면 가담자였어?

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Insight]</Start> You're trapped here too, aren't you...
You tell me 'bout da Jharegs...
"Charade?" What this you speak of?
Did you do this crime or only watch?
Text: 너 범죄 저질렀어 아니면 그냥 봤어?

TextEng: Argue your guilt or innocence while you still can...
Text: 아직 시간 있을 때 네 죄에 대해 말해봐...

TextEng: You be guilty of da crime here? Yes or no?
Text: 너 여기서 범죄 저질렀어? 응 아니 아니?

TextEng: Tell me more...
Get to the point.
Ooh, you talk more...
You got point? Get to it.
Then it was you behind the slaughter!?
But why did you do this?
Text: 하지만 왜 이런 짓을 한 거야?

TextEng: Why are you telling me this so openly?
Will you give this as your written oath?
Huh? You was behind da slaughter!?
How come you do all this?
Why you be so honest, all of sudden?
You gives this as written oath, yuh?
